# Deploy to Production

After completing any code change in this project:

1. Run `npm run build` and fix failures before deploying.
2. Commit all relevant changes with a clear message (never commit `.env` or secrets).
3. Push to `origin/main` — Vercel deploys production from `main` at `www.sunshines88.com`.
4. Confirm the push succeeded (`git status` shows up to date with `origin/main`).
5. Tell the user when deploy was triggered and what was included.

Do not skip deploy unless the user explicitly says not to deploy that change.
